ce:section.ce:para:
The color of T. bispinosa peel extract transformed to greenish brown after heating at 90°C for 120min due to the formation of C-dots. This is mainly due to the thermal oxidation of precursors present in the extract of T. bispinosa. Brown color of the solution appeared extremely fluorescent under UV-light (λex
                     =365nm) exhibiting deep green fluorescence (inset of Fig. 1
                     ). Fluorescence in C-dots may appear due to the recombination of electron–hole pair from impurity atoms and oxygen bearing functional groups [2]. However, the exact mechanism of origin of multicolored luminescence is still a brain child.
